<emphasis box="[947,1050,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">khuludae</emphasis>
”, only male) (
<collectingCountry box="[1213,1290,721,747]" name="Jordan" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Jordan</collectingCountry>
(Lower Cretaceous)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="413" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,721,1432]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,793,819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kaddumi, H. F." box="[326,509,793,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" refId="ref14526" refString="Kaddumi, H. F. (2005) The Amber of Jordan. The Oldest Prehistoric Insects in Fossilized Resin. 2 nd Edition. Eternal River Museum of Natural History, Amman, 224 pp." type="book" year="2005">Kaddumi (2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaddumi, H. F." box="[525,583,793,819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" refId="ref14564" refString="Kaddumi, H. F. (2007) The Amber of Jordan. The Oldest Prehistoric Insects in Fossilized Resin. 3 rd Edition. Eternal River Museum of Natural History, Amman, 298 pp." type="book" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
) distinguished this genus to include a single species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaddumi" authorityYear="2005" box="[1216,1336,793,820]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Curvus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khuludi">
<emphasis box="[1216,1235,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1252,1336,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">khuludi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(also as “ 
<emphasis box="[164,267,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">khuludae</emphasis>
”), described from the amber of 
<collectingCountry box="[638,716,829,855]" name="Jordan" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Jordan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[728,793,830,856]" country="Jordan" name="Az Zarqa'" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Zarqa</collectingRegion>
River basin, Lower Cretaceous (between 124–140 Ma). However, proper comparison of this taxon with other groups of microphorines was not provided.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,721,1432]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">
According to the original description, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaddumi" authorityYear="2005" box="[627,799,901,928]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Curvus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khuludi">
<emphasis box="[627,799,901,928]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Curvus khuludi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all fossil microphorines primarily by an eye covered with ommatrichia. This condition is considered as apomorphic (but highly homoplasious) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[1301,1436,937,963]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Empidoidea">Empidoidea</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[217,570,973,999]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 172" refId="ref16254" refString="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2006) The morphology, higher-level phylogeny and classification of the Empidoidea (Diptera). Zootaxa, 1180 (1), 1 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1180.1.1" type="journal article" year="2006">Sinclair &amp; Cumming 2006: 21</bibRefCitation>
, character 2). Within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[821,1000,973,999]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dolichopodidae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1010,1125,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">
<taxonomicName box="[1010,1072,974,999]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensu">sensu</taxonomicName>
lato
</emphasis>
this character is present in the most 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chvála" authorityYear="1981" box="[256,436,1009,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Parathalassiinae">Parathalassiinae</taxonomicName>
(except extinct 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Negrobov" authorityYear="1978" box="[619,824,1009,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Cretomicrophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[619,824,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Cretomicrophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Negrobov" authorityYear="1978" box="[838,1007,1009,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Archichrysotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[838,1007,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Archichrysotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Negrobov" authorityYear="1978" box="[1063,1163,1010,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Retinitus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1063,1163,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Retinitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[1187,1366,1009,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dolichopodidae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">
<taxonomicName box="[1374,1436,1010,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensu">sensu</taxonomicName>
stricto
</emphasis>
, as well as in some recent species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1902" box="[639,872,1045,1071]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Schistostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[639,787,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Schistostoma</emphasis>
Becker
</taxonomicName>
of the microphorines (
<bibRefCitation author="Shamshev, I. V. &amp; Sinclair, B. J." box="[1126,1432,1045,1071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref16072" refString="Shamshev, I. V. &amp; Sinclair, B. J. (2006) The genus Schistostoma Becker from southern Africa, with an evaluation of its generic status (Diptera: Dolichopodidae s. l.: Microphorinae). African Invertebrates, 47, 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2006">Shamshev &amp; Sinclair 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shamshev, I. V." box="[151,336,1081,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="303 - 306" refId="ref16124" refString="Shamshev, I. V. (2020) First record of an extant species of the genus Schistostoma Becker (Diptera: Dolichopodidae: Microphorinae) from the Oriental Region. Russian Entomological Journal, 29 (3), 303 - 306. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 29.3.11" type="journal article" year="2020">Shamshev 2020</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cumming, J. M. &amp; Brooks, S. E." box="[350,655,1081,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="111 - 129" refId="ref13905" refString="Cumming, J. M. &amp; Brooks, S. E. (2019) Phylogenetic analysis and preliminary classification of the Parathalassiinae (Diptera: Empidoidea: Dolichopodidae sensu lato). Zootaxa, 4648 (1), 111 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4648.1.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Cumming &amp; Brooks 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brooks, S. E. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[670,976,1081,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref13522" refString="Brooks, S. E. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2022) Revision of the Nearctic Microphorinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae sensu lato). Zootaxa, 5095 (1), 1 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5095.1.1" type="journal article" year="2022">Brooks &amp; Cumming 2022</bibRefCitation>
). The compound eyes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaddumi" authorityYear="2005" box="[1272,1392,1081,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Curvus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khuludi">
<emphasis box="[1272,1291,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1308,1392,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">khuludi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are rather dichoptic (apomorphic). The author noted that “frons narrow and decreasing in width toward antennae, eyes meet above antennae” (i.e., eye margins converging toward antennae) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaddumi, H. F." box="[961,1195,1153,1179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" refId="ref14564" refString="Kaddumi, H. F. (2007) The Amber of Jordan. The Oldest Prehistoric Insects in Fossilized Resin. 3 rd Edition. Eternal River Museum of Natural History, Amman, 298 pp." type="book" year="2007">Kaddumi 2007: 122</bibRefCitation>
). This condition may resemble that described in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="1999" box="[449,584,1189,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Avenaphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,584,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Avenaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[638,831,1189,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Pristinmicrophor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[638,831,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Pristinmicrophor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although, in both these genera the eyes are separated by the frons above the antennae and ommatidia are equally small. In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaddumi" authorityYear="2005" box="[1022,1138,1225,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Curvus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khuludi">
<emphasis box="[1022,1041,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1054,1138,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">khuludi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses unusually short, subtriangular postpedicel. However, a similarly short postpedicel was described in the Upper Cretaceous (Burmese amber) 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ngo-Muller et al. 2020)" baseAuthorityName="Ngo-Muller" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[237,786,1297,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphorites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pouilloni">
<emphasis box="[237,503,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Microphorites pouilloni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ngo-Muller, V. &amp; Garrouste, R. &amp; Pouillon, J. - M. &amp; Nel, A." box="[517,779,1297,1324]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref15786" refString="Ngo-Muller, V., Garrouste, R., Pouillon, J. - M. &amp; Nel, A. (2020) A new species of the long-legged fly genus Microphorites in Burmese amber (Dolichopodidae: Microphorinae). Cretaceous Research, 107, 1 - 4. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2019.104284" type="journal article" year="2020">
Ngô-Muller 
<emphasis box="[659,708,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and in the recent 
<taxonomicName authority="(Shamshev 2020)" baseAuthorityName="Shamshev" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[983,1433,1297,1323]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Schistostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis box="[983,1227,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Schistostoma indicum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shamshev, I. V." box="[1241,1425,1297,1323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" pagination="303 - 306" refId="ref16124" refString="Shamshev, I. V. (2020) First record of an extant species of the genus Schistostoma Becker (Diptera: Dolichopodidae: Microphorinae) from the Oriental Region. Russian Entomological Journal, 29 (3), 303 - 306. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 29.3.11" type="journal article" year="2020">Shamshev 2020</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The wing venation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaddumi" authorityYear="2005" box="[403,520,1333,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Curvus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khuludi">
<emphasis box="[403,422,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[436,520,1333,1359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">khuludi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to match with that of the 
<taxonomicName box="[910,1030,1333,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Microphor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
